#TsekCorona! is a music video with a positive stay-at-home message from South Africa during the country's Covid-19 lockdown. It features rewritten lyrics to the hit song "Welcome to Cape Town" by original writer, David Kramer. JOHANNESBURG - It's Day 12 of the national lockdown and some South Africans are starting to feel the blues. But don’t despair! Some of the country’s most talented musicians have collaborated to produce a song to keep us entertained. COVID-19: Cure likely to be found before a vaccine - expert The likes of David Kramer and Emo Adams have come up with a twist to the popular song “Welcome to Cape Town”. The song comes with a funny and positive message to beat the coronavirus. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.